<p>
Thank you Ryan. I hd tried HDR before, but did it all wrong by trying to get the image right too early. Thanks for your tutorial, now I know how to do it. A suggestion: I tried direct import of the RAW files, and import of the TIFFS translated via Adobe Lightroom with a constant regulation of colour temperature (all the rest was zero). The TIFF files worked much better, I believe due to superior translation of Lightroom. I also found that curve adjusting is better done in Photoshop after the translation to 16 bit.<br />Fabio
