<dd class='comment-body' id='Blog1_cmt-5482755561377550171'>
<p>
I have to say I disagree with your assessment of Photomatix.  My <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/richietown/sets/72157594234514295/">photos</a> photos are all done with Photomatix and come out quite realistically.  You're right that many people take HDR to the extreme and their results are cartoony, but with practice and an artistic eye, the results can be great!  In my experience with HDR images in Photoshop CS2, the results are much grainier and dull than with Photomatix.  Thanks for the post!
</p>
</dd>
