<p>
I am hoping HDR will be moot pretty soon. Theoretically with a digital camera they can make a camera where EACH pixel is exposed and shuttered individually. Giving you essentially perfect dynamic range. we just need someone to invent this in a practical manner :-) every HDR shot I have seen so far is simple stunning !! I never dreamed of doing it this way. in the past I would shoot one for land once for sky and "merge" them in photoshop something which I was never overly adept at. they looked MUCH better than either seperate image but you could tell they were "put" together. These shots are simply stunning !! I can not wait to start playing with this software. Going to do some shooting this weekend!
</p>
