<p>
That's definately true, QT!  HDR has its limitations, that's for sure.  I, too, also do a lot of layer-masking work; it's actually the method that I prefer for most shots.  But there are some shots where HDR really, really works.  <br /><br />I think that the look of HDR downsampled images will improve dramatically over the next few years as software companies refine their tone-mapping functions.
</p>
