<dd class='comment-body' id='Blog1_cmt-9173097201270900645'>
<p>
It definitely is an interesting article!<BR/><BR/>But I'm with Ryan on this one. Through Photoshop you can achieve a lot cleaner and "realistic" looking images than through photomatix.<BR/><BR/>Well, I shouldn't even say that. It is up to the skill of each individual as you can tweak the image any way you want. <BR/><BR/>If Pete wants plasticy looking images that are dramatic but kind of make you go "what's wrong with it", hey - his choice. <BR/>I prefer the well-balanced and rich  images that are simply pleasant to look at. <BR/><BR/>Pete's images are awesome in their angles and motives, but the color and contrast simply throw me off.
</p>
